key_points: Gabby Petito, 22, was reported missing after her fiancé, Brian Laundrie, returned from a road trip without her.
The couple had embarked on a cross-country trip in a van, but Petito went missing in September.
Bodycam footage from Moab, Utah, showed an emotional Petito after a reported domestic dispute.
A 911 call reported Laundrie slapping Petito, but police suggested they separate for the night.
Laundrie flew to Tampa from Salt Lake City on Aug. 17 and returned on Aug. 23.
Petito's family lost contact with her in late August, doubting a text message sent on Aug. 30 was really from her.
Petito was found dead in Grand Teton National Park on Sept. 19, cause of death was manual strangulation.
Brian Laundrie was reported missing by his parents on Sept. 17 and found dead from a self-inflicted gunshot in Carlton Reserve weeks later.
A notebook was found near Laundrie's remains, but its contents have not been revealed.
The case garnered national interest and sparked discussions about domestic violence and missing persons investigations.
